<FIRST>u i PM-Soviet-Hostages     08-01 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Soviet-Hostages,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviets Denounce Reported Hanging of Higgins, Fault Israel</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Hostages, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union today denounced the reported
hanging of Lt. Col. William R. Higgins in Lebanon as ``inhuman'',
but also faulted Israel for kidnapping Shiite Moslem cleric Sheikh
Abdul Karim Obeid.
   Foreign Ministry spokesman Vadim Perfiliev read out a brief
statement at a hastily called news briefing saying, ``We resolutely
denounce this inhuman action.''
   A pro-Iranian group, the Organization of the Oppressed on Earth,
said it hanged the U.S. Marine on Monday because Israel refused to
release Obeid, who was abducted from his south Lebanon home on
Friday.
   ``The fact that the aggravation of the situation in Lebanon,
caused specifically by the abduction of Shiite leader Sheikh Obeid
by Israeli commandos, has led to an escalation of acts of violence
and terror and evokes profound concern,'' the statement said.
   ``The Soviet Union regards such actions as a gross violation of
human rights and dangerous for the whole international
atmosphere,'' it said.
   Soviet Foreign Minister Eduard Shevardnadze, currently in Tehran
on an official visit, will take up the matter of Higgins' reported
death with Iranian officials, Perfiliev said, without elaboration.
</TEXT>
