<HEAD>17 Dead, Including Family of 10, in Helicopter Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A military helicopter crashed in a
thunderstorm and killed all 17 people aboard, including a colonel
and nine members of his family, the army said today.
   Victims of Monday's crash included three brigadiers, or one-star
generals, in addition to Col. Abdel-Latif Bushara Ahmed and his
family, the army said.
   Senior officers often use military transportation for family
members because of the unreliability of civilian transport in this
East African country.
   A statement from military headquarters said the aircraft crashed
during a 260-mile flight to Khartoum from Kassala in eastern Sudan
near the Ethiopian border. It gave no details about where it
crashed.
   The statement said the helicopter, piloted by a brigadier, flew
into the thunderstorm and crashed. Storms with strong winds lashed
Khartoum on Monday night.
