<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Uganda-Rustlers     08-01 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Uganda-Rustlers,0093</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cattle Rustlers Abducting People To Work Their Gardens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cattle rustlers who have been known to
abduct people to look after their herds now have taken captives to
tend their gardens, a newspaper reported Tuesday.
   The rustlers, Karamajong tribesmen, killed three of the 50
people who have been abducted since June in northeastern Uganda,
the New Vision newspaper said. The rustlers also stole nearly 200
head of cattle, it said.
   Thirteen of the captives were set free after working for a week,
it said.
</TEXT>
