<HEAD>Tobacco Workers Protest U.S. Cigarette Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 35 members of a tobacco workers'
union shouted ``Americans, go home!'' in front of the U.S. Embassy
on Tuesday to protest attempts by U.S. companies to enter the
protected local market.
   ``If the smoker has to die, they should die with Thai tobacco,''
said a leaflet distributed by the demonstrators from the Thailand
Tobacco Monopoly Labor Union.
   They left behind a funeral wreath that said: ``The Tobacco Labor
Union condemns the U.S. for bringing death to Thai people.''
