<FIRST>r a AM-TripleDrowning     08-01 0217</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Triple Drowning,0222</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Brothers, Sister, Drown in Arroyo Pond</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PINEDALE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man and his younger sister and brother
accidentally drowned in a pond of rainwater that accumulated in an
arroyo, authorities said.
   Larryington Miller, 26; Thelma Ann Miller, 23; and Toby Miller,
15, drowned Monday about 1{ miles northeast of Pinedale in rural
western New Mexico, said Alex Ashley, a deputy state medical
investigator.
   The brothers apparently found the pond that formed at the bottom
of a drop in the arroyo where water had carved a depression in the
sandstone and mud, Ashley said Tuesday.
   Ms. Miller found Toby floating in the water, so she sent her
newphews home to get help, Ashley said. Relatives arrived to find
her body floating, Ashley said.
   Navajo police and other officials were told by the family that
Larryington's clothes were on the side of the pond but they could
not find him, Ashley said. Fire and rescue personnel found
Larryington's body underwater, Ashley said.
   ``I think maybe the younger one jumped in and started drowning,
so the older brother jumped in to help,'' Ashley said. ``Then the
girl jumped in to try to help the other two.''
   Runoff from summer rain probably is creating ponds that can be
dangerous throughout rural New Mexico, he said.
