<SECOND>AM-Karajan,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Conductor Left `Musical Legacy' of 40 Recordings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Austrian conductor Herbert von
Karajan, who died July 16 at age 81, left about 40 recordings of
concerts and operas as his ``musical legacy,'' the Swiss executor
of his will said Tuesday.
   Lawyer Werner Kupper said the first three recordings were
expected to be released before Christmas.
   He declined comment on the financial dispositions of the will,
which was opened Monday at Samaden, near St. Moritz, where Karajan
had a residence.
   The fortune of the conductor, who is survived by his wife,
Eoeliette, and two daughters, has been estimated in published
reports at about $242 million. There was no word from Swiss and
Austrian authorities on the inheritance tax claims.
