<TEXT>
   Forty parents burst into applause Tuesday
as a judge ordered a school bus driver held without bail on charges
of molesting a 13-year-old boy for almost three years.
   Robert Izzo, 39, of Hicksville, a former Boy Scout leader,
pleaded innocent in Nassau County Court on a 20-count indictment
charging him with sex abuse, sodomy and endangering the welfare of
a child.
   Izzo, who also is charged with abusing a 5-year-old girl, is
being investigated in as many as 20 other reported incidents of
molestations, police say.
