million bail, citing a strong case and an ongoing investigation.
   When County Judge Marvin Goodman announced that Izzo was to be
held without bail pending a pre-probation report Friday, parents
shrieked and applauded.
   Izzo was arrested May 21 and charged with sexually abusing the
boy from 1986 to 1988, allegedly on buses parked in the garage of
Harran Bus Transportation, where Izzo was employed, and in Izzo's
car and home.
   He was released on $20,000 bail but was rearrested last month
when he was charged with abusing a 5-year-old girl who rode his
bus. A grand jury is soon to begin hearing evidence in the girl's
case.
