   Major commercial banks trimmed their prime
lending rates a half percentage point to 10.5 percent, highlighting
the trend toward lower interest rates that has accompanied
continued signs of slower economic growth.
   The reductions Monday followed a similar move three weeks ago by
Chase Manhattan Bank and one Friday by San Francisco-based Bank of
America.
