<HEAD>Bridgestone Consolidates Tire Headquarters In Akron</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bridgestone Corp., which last year merged
with Firestone Tire &amp; Rubber Co., said today it was consolidating
its tire business under a new name and corporate headquarters.
   The merged company will be known as Bridgestone-Firestone Inc.,
the company said.
   Although Firestone's corporate headquarters is in Chicago and
Bridgestone's U.S. unit is in Nashville, the new company will be
based in Akron, where Firestone was founded in 1900.
   John J. Nevin, Firestone chairman and chief executive officer,
will serve as chairman of Bridgestone-Firestone until he is
scheduled to retire next year, the company said.
   Tokyo-based Bridgestone completed its $2.6 billion acquisition
of Firestone last April, and Firestone became Bridgestone's wholly
owned subsidiary.
